      "content": "I understand your frustration with warfarin, but switching to a more natural approach isn't recommended, especially when it comes to anticoagulants. Garlic may have some anticoagulant properties, but it's not safe to replace warfarin with it, as it could increase the risk of bleeding. It's essential to consult your doctor before making any changes to your medication or diet. They can help you explore safer and more effective options if that's a concern without compromising your health.",
